---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="resume -- alexander campos" description="Operations background, self-taught engineer. Capital One, Guardian, ForgeFrame, Reframed.">
  <article class="resume">
    <h1>Resume</h1>

    <section class="summary">
      <p>
        Operations background, self-taught engineer. Led process modernization across a $600M+
        regulatory operation at Capital One. Built and open-sourced AI infrastructure —
        model routing, semantic memory, cognitive safety tooling — to solve problems the
        existing tools didn't cover. Published computational neuroscience research (GL-001, under review).
        Shipped commercial products. The work spans both sides because the interesting problems do.
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Skills</h2>

      <h3>Operations & Systems</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Process Modernization · Failure-Surface Mapping · Dependency Sequencing ·
        KPI/OKR Frameworks · Executive Reporting · Regulatory Compliance (NCUA, CFPB)
      </p>

      <h3>Data</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        SQL (Postgres, Snowflake) · Python (Pandas) · Splunk · Pipeline Monitoring ·
        Looker Studio · QuickSight · Power BI
      </p>

      <h3>Development</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        TypeScript · React · Node.js · Electron · Next.js · Astro · SQLite/FTS5 · Vite · Zustand
      </p>

      <h3>AI Infrastructure</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Multi-Provider LLM Routing (Anthropic/OpenAI/Ollama) · Model Context Protocol ·
        Structured Tool-Use · Semantic Memory · Streaming SSE · Local-First Architecture
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Salesforce · JIRA · Confluence · SLA Governance · Vendor Risk Management · Change Control
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Experience</h2>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Capital One -- Senior Process Manager, Card Legal Recoveries Operations</h3>
          <span class="dates">June 2025 -- Present | Richmond, VA</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Built the monitoring system for a $600M+ file exchange network</strong> --
            300+ daily regulatory transmissions, no unified failure tracking. Rapid prototype
            (SQL/Sheets/Looker) evolved into automated anomaly detection. Reduced manual
            monitoring by 78%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Resolved a 20,000+ account logic failure</strong> while the Data team was
            backlogged 6+ weeks. Built an investigative SQL framework, isolated root cause,
            remediated accounts, documented the failure taxonomy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Zero transmission errors during $35B Discover merger integration.</strong>
            Owned the Systems Integration Guide -- caught specification failures with Engineering
            and vendor partners before production cutover.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Authored a 5-month modernization roadmap</strong> -- dependency sequencing,
            stakeholder gates, rollback protocols. Full visibility for leadership before
            resource commitment.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Self-learned infrastructure tooling</strong> (Splunk, Postgres, JSON parsing)
            to close a gap between Process and Engineering. Built a real-time validation layer.
            Unblocked 6 months of stalled monitoring work.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Automated business reviews</strong> across 3 teams and 6 operational vectors.
            Standardized one-pagers now used by department leaders three levels up for quarterly reviews.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Operationalized Gemini as a structured reporting tool</strong> before the org
            had an AI playbook. Scoped instruction sets with validated formulas. Operational AI,
            not conversational.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Independent Engineering -- Open Source</h3>
          <span class="dates">June 2025 -- Present</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Building tools to solve problems I keep hitting at work -- privacy, cost, context loss,
          vendor lock-in. Teaching myself the engineering. Everything is open-source, live, and verifiable.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Shipped a resume analysis platform end-to-end</strong> -- live at
            <a href="https://reframed.works">reframed.works</a>. Stripe payments, magic-link auth,
            streaming analysis. 34 API routes, multi-provider routing with fallback chains,
            voice fingerprinting, 14 industry format profiles. Sole developer, architecture
            through deployment.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built a local-first AI desktop application</strong> (Electron, React, Node.js) --
            chat, terminal, notes, knowledge graph. 50+ IPC channels, 20 backend modules. Five-stage
            post-chat pipeline: awareness detection, summarization, embeddings, knowledge graph,
            auto-extraction. Supports air-gapped local inference.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed a model routing engine</strong> -- open-source TypeScript package.
            Tier-based dispatch across Anthropic, OpenAI, and Ollama. Intent detection, SSE
            normalization, cost optimization (40-60% reduction).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built a semantic memory system</strong> (SQLite/FTS5) with hierarchical
            compression. Shipped as an MCP server with 12 tools. Works with Claude Desktop,
            Cursor, and any MCP client.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built cognitive safety tooling</strong> -- reframe detection across 7 influence
            types and 8 identity dimensions, awareness-trap detection for recurring unresolved
            patterns. Integrated into the desktop pipeline. Local-only.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Apple Federal Credit Union -- Branch Operations Administrator</h3>
          <span class="dates">January 2020 -- May 2025 | Fairfax, VA</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Promoted four times in five years</strong> -- teller to enterprise support
            across 25 branches during a major merger. Completed bachelor's degree concurrently.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built compliance tracking infrastructure</strong> -- Power BI dashboards
            for VP-level reporting, regulatory documentation (NCUA, CFPB). Reduced complaint
            response cycles by 50%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed a branch-wide modernization roadmap</strong> -- presented to the
            CEO with VP and SVP backing. Approved and moved into active implementation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>B.S. Business Administration, Management and Operations</strong> -- George Mason
        University, December 2024.
      </p>
      <p class="skills">Certifications: Business Process Management · Google Data Analytics</p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <div class="resume-contact">
      <p><a href="mailto:alex@campos.works">alex@campos.works</a> · <a href="tel:+17036253586">(703) 625-3586</a> · <a href="https://campos.works">campos.works</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c you are reading the resume of someone who builds systems like this one. ',
      'color: #5BF29B; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .resume {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .skills {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--white-60);
  }

  .role {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .role-header {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role-header h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .dates {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
  }

  .role ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .role li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role li strong {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
  }

  .resume-contact {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .resume-contact p {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
  }
</style>
